# Documentation Rules

References:

- docs/product-requirements.md
- docs/database-design.md
- docs/enums.md
- docs/user-flows.md
- docs/api-specification.md
- docs/tech-architecture.md
- docs/coding-standards.md
- docs/folder-structure.md
- docs/development-roadmap.md
- docs/deployment-guide.md

---

# Documentation Philosophy

Documentation is part of the product.

Code and documentation must remain synchronized.

Outdated documentation is considered a defect.

---

# Source Of Truth

The following documents are authoritative:

Product Requirements

```text
docs/product-requirements.md
```

Database

```text
docs/database-design.md
```

Enums

```text
docs/enums.md
```

API

```text
docs/api-specification.md
```

Architecture

```text
docs/tech-architecture.md
```

---

# Documentation First Rule

Before implementing:

- New Feature
- New Entity
- New Module
- New API
- New Database Table

Verify whether documentation must be updated.

---

# Product Requirements Rules

Update:

```text
docs/product-requirements.md
```

When:

- New business feature added
- Existing feature behavior changes
- User flow changes

---

# Database Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/database-design.md
```

When:

- New table added
- New column added
- Relationship changes
- Constraints change

Never modify database schema without updating documentation.

---

# Enum Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/enums.md
```

When:

- New enum added
- Enum values change
- Enum descriptions change

Never introduce undocumented enum values.

---

# API Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/api-specification.md
```

When:

- New endpoint added
- Endpoint removed
- Request changes
- Response changes

API documentation must remain current.

---

# User Flow Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/user-flows.md
```

When:

- User journey changes
- Screen flow changes
- Business process changes

---

# Architecture Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/tech-architecture.md
```

When:

- New architectural pattern introduced
- New layer introduced
- Deployment architecture changes

---

# Roadmap Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/development-roadmap.md
```

When:

- Sprint scope changes
- Feature priority changes
- MVP scope changes

---

# Deployment Documentation Rules

Update:

```text
docs/deployment-guide.md
```

When:

- Infrastructure changes
- Environment variables change
- Deployment process changes

---

# Documentation Quality Rules

Documentation must be:

- Clear
- Concise
- Actionable
- Up-to-date

Avoid:

- Ambiguous descriptions
- Duplicate content
- Outdated screenshots

---

# Markdown Standards

Use:

```markdown
# Heading 1

## Heading 2

### Heading 3
```

Prefer lists over large paragraphs.

---

# Example Documentation Trigger

If a new entity is created:

Example:

```text
Referral
```

Required updates:

✓ database-design.md

✓ enums.md

✓ product-requirements.md

✓ api-specification.md

✓ user-flows.md

---

# AI Assistant Responsibilities

Before completing a feature:

Check whether any documentation updates are required.

If required:

List affected documentation files.

---

# Code Generation Checklist

✓ Documentation reviewed

✓ Documentation updated if necessary

✓ API docs synchronized

✓ Database docs synchronized

✓ Enums documented

✓ User flows synchronized

✓ Roadmap updated if scope changes

Documentation consistency is mandatory.
